This Food Loft coffee shop has spacious seating area, the seating outside the coffee shop is airy.

There is a vegetarian stall ÂìÅÂë≥Á¥†È£üÔºåserving nice vegetarian foods. As early as 9 am, they too serve fried Ho Fan.

One of our favourite place from Clementi neighbourhood! Always frequent their roasted stall for charsiew/roasted meat rice abc/white raddish/watercress/lotus root soupüòç; thai stall's seafood fried rice/sambal kangkung/tomyum/brazil minced meat (some dishes so so); collins mixed grill and aglio olio. And newly tried bbq stall's seafood fried rice big portion! The other stalls either never tried before, or so so. When we don't don't know where to have our lunch/dinner, there we go/dabao.
Tried the Thai food place. Food rating - fried pork 3/5, prawn omelette 3/5 and mango salad 3/5. Price is reasonable for Thai food. Place is not too crowded and not noisy.
Just your regular neighbourhood coffee shop. What's special is that there is a Thai food stall here instead of the more commonly found Zi Char stall.
A place with a variety of food, however, places are a little difficult to find during peak hours
